articles.author: Filip Cleeren
articles.title: Alonso eyeing podium after "amazing" Bahrain F1 qualifying - Motorsport.com
articles.description: Fernando Alonso thinks he has a chance to fight for the podium in Formula 1's Bahrain Grand Prix after being buoyed by his "amazing" fifth place in qualifying which "felt too good to be true."
articles.content:
Alonso and his Aston Martin team were the talk of the paddock after topping for FP2 and FP3, with the expectation that the Silverstone team could at least challenge Mercedes to enter the top three.
